All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
BFS
Breadth-First Search (BFS) algorithm for finding the minimum path between two nodes in an Internet graph.
CacheMinDistances
A cache for storing and retrieving minimum distances between nodes in an Internet graph.
CsvReader
 
CsvWriter
 
Dijkstra
Dijkstra's algorithm for finding the minimum path and distances from a source node to all other nodes in an Internet graph.
Dijkstra.DijkstraResult
Result of Dijkstra's algorithm, containing distances and predecessors.
Edge
The Edge class represents a connection between two nodes in a graph, with properties such as direction, response time, and geolocation data.
GeoIP2
The GeoIP2 class implements the GeolocationService interface to provide geolocation data based on IP addresses using the GeoIP2 database.
GeolocationData
The GeolocationData class represents geographical coordinates and location information, including latitude, longitude, country, and city.
GeolocationData.TypedGeolocationData
A nested class representing typed geolocation data, including the service generating the data and an optional GeolocationData object.
GeolocationService
The GeolocationService interface defines the contract for a service that provides geolocation information based on IP addresses.
GetGeolocationDataHandlerSax
The GetGeolocationDataHandlerSax class is a SAX (Simple API for XML) handler used to parse XML data and extract geolocation information such as country name, city name, and coordinates.
HostIP
The HostIP class implements the GeolocationService interface to provide geolocation data based on host IP addresses using a SAX parser.
InternetCartographier
The InternetCartographier class represents a tool for mapping the Internet graph based on traceroute results, geolocation services, and specified weight metrics.
InternetGraph
The InternetGraph class represents a graph of nodes and edges, modeling the structure of an internet network.
IPAddress
The IPAddress class represents an IP address and provides utility methods for working with IP addresses.
Node
The Node class represents a node in an internet graph with an IP address and associated geolocation data.
Path<T>
Represents a path in a graph with elements of type T.
PropertiesSingleton
Singleton class for managing properties loaded from a configuration file.
Statistic
An abstract class representing a statistical measure related to an InternetCartographier.
Test
 
WeightMetric
Enumeration representing different weight metrics for edges in a network graph.
